      "comment": "ZIPPING PFEIFFER (1) has a strong record here with five wins and two placings from eight starts. Missed the frame latest (30.60) when sixth over 520m at Wentworth Park in a Grade 5. Looks well placed and should feature. DAISY'S CHARM (2) was game in defeat off the inside draw last start, finishing second and beaten 1.75 lengths (29.77) behind Cessnock Curtain at this track. Expected to feature. TARAWI MALIBU (4) was never in contention last time after missing the jump at Gosford, but prior to that won by 1.3 lengths at Wentworth Park (30.08) beating Fantastic Elle in a Grade 5 on January 31. A big run wouldn't surprise. PIRATE RIOT (3) placed last time out at big odds - worth considering.",
